Preheat the #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pop the @butternut squash{1}(diced) onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Couscous ==

Add the @couscous{100%grams} and half the @chicken stock{1%sachet} to a #bowl{}.

Pour in 200ml boiling @water{to taste} and mix well to combine.

Cover with a #plate{} or cling film and leave aside for ~{10%minutes} (or until ready to serve).

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Tagine ==

Meanwhile, place a large pan over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @almonds{15%grams} until lightly toasted, stirring regularly, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated).

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Use a #teaspoon{} to easily scrape away the peel.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the onion and @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fry until chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the ginger and garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Pour in the @passata{1%pack}, remaining stock, 50ml water and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Cover and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir through a knob of @butter{to taste}, the @harissa paste{1%sachet} and roasted butternut squash.

Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if necessary. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken and butternut squash tagine.

Finish with a sprinkling of toasted almonds and a drizzle of @cranberry chutney{1%sachet}.